RIYADH: Saudi Arabia's crude oil exports grew 147,000 barrels per day in April to 7.38 million, according to the latest monthly data released by the Joint Organisations Data Initiative. This is the highest monthly level of volume since March 2020 when the Kingdom’s exports were 7.39 million bpd. Exports of crude rose by 2 percent in April from 7.24 million bpd in March 2022. Year-on-year, the Kingdom's shipments of crude abroad surged by 1.97 million bpd — an increase of 36.5 percent. As for the production of crude, in April it grew by 141,000 bpd to 10.44 million bpd. Production rose by 1.4 percent from 10.3 million bpd in March.